text: Ursula Birkholz (ne√© Ursula Fenselau, born 9 January 1911) was a German track and field athlete specialized in the 80 metres hurdles event. She was a member of Dresdner SC and represented Germany at international competitions. Birkholz won the bronze medal at the 1930 Women's World Games in the 80 metres hurdles event. At the national championships she won the silver medal in the 80 metres hurdles event at the behind Gerda Pirch.
